<subSubSection id="C320652A4544FFA82F20FEFC6F70FDB7" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B8536A14544FFA82F20FEFC6F70FDB7" blockId="3.[808,1448,364,548]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis id="B94EEAB34544FFA82F20FEFC68E4FE17" bold="true" box="[808,948,364,388]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis id="B94EEAB34544FFA82F20FEFC68C6FE17" bold="true" box="[808,918,364,388]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. –
</emphasis>
The species can be easily separated from 
<taxonomicName id="4C3A4D224544FFA82999FEFD6F0EFE37" authority="(Song &amp; Kim, 1992)" authorityName="Tang &amp; Yin &amp; Peng &amp; Griswold" authorityYear="2009" baseAuthorityName="Song &amp; Kim" baseAuthorityYear="1992" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Cupa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gongi">
<emphasis id="B94EEAB34544FFA82999FEFD6836FE37" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">E. gongi</emphasis>
(Song &amp; Kim, 1992)
</taxonomicName>
by: female with larger body size: 7.36–7.62 (6.00– 
<quantity id="4CC29B444544FFA82817FE3D6F3EFE57" box="[1055,1134,429,452]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6764" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" unit="in" value="6.6">6.60 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName id="4C3A4D224544FFA82870FE3D6F86FE57" authorityName="Tang &amp; Yin &amp; Peng &amp; Griswold" authorityYear="2009" baseAuthorityName="Song &amp; Kim" baseAuthorityYear="1992" box="[1144,1238,429,452]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Cupa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gongi">
<emphasis id="B94EEAB34544FFA82870FE3D6F86FE57" box="[1144,1238,429,452]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">E. gongi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); copulatory ducts curved and tube-shaped (short and straight in 
<taxonomicName id="4C3A4D224544FFA8293FFE5D6EC7FE77" authorityName="Tang &amp; Yin &amp; Peng &amp; Griswold" authorityYear="2009" baseAuthorityName="Song &amp; Kim" baseAuthorityYear="1992" box="[1335,1431,461,484]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Cupa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gongi">
<emphasis id="B94EEAB34544FFA8293FFE5D6EC7FE77" box="[1335,1431,461,484]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">E. gongi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); spermathecae small and spherical (spermathecae with 2 chambers in 
<taxonomicName id="4C3A4D224544FFA82FBCFD9D6F41FDB7" authorityName="Tang &amp; Yin &amp; Peng &amp; Griswold" authorityYear="2009" baseAuthorityName="Song &amp; Kim" baseAuthorityYear="1992" box="[948,1041,525,548]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Cupa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gongi">
<emphasis id="B94EEAB34544FFA82FBCFD9D6F41FDB7" box="[948,1041,525,548]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">E. gongi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
