<subSubSection id="C320652A4544FFA82F20FA7C68BAF877" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B8536A14544FFA82F20FA7C68BAF877" blockId="3.[808,1448,1516,2020]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis id="B94EEAB34544FFA82F20FA7C68F9F997" bold="true" box="[808,937,1516,1540]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis id="B94EEAB34544FFA82F20FA7C68DAF997" bold="true" box="[808,906,1516,1540]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Remarks</emphasis>
. –
</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus id="548188034544FFA82FEFFA7D6F45F997" box="[999,1045,1517,1540]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">type</typeStatus>
specimen of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3A4D224544FFA828B8FA7D6EF8F997" authorityName="Tikader" authorityYear="1970" box="[1200,1448,1517,1540]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Platythomisus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bazarus">
<emphasis id="B94EEAB34544FFA828B8FA7D6EF8F997" box="[1200,1448,1517,1540]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Platythomisus bazarus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was kept in ZSI and is unavailable for study by foreign arachnologists (
<bibRefCitation id="EFAB4B504544FFA82FD8F9BD6FFEF9D7" author="Lehtinen, P" box="[976,1198,1581,1604]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" pagination="147 - 184" refId="ref6350" refString="Lehtinen, P. T., 2004. Taxonomic notes on the Misumenini (Araneae: Thomisidae: Thomisinae), primarily from the Palaearctic and Oriental regions. In Logunov, D. V. &amp; D. Penney (eds.), European Arachnology 2003 (Proceedings of the 21 st European Colloquium of Arachnology, St. - Petersburg, 4 - 9 August 2003). Arthropoda Selecta, Special Issue, 1: 147 - 184." type="journal article" year="2004">Lehtinen, 2004: 178</bibRefCitation>
). However, the locality of one of our specimens (Lataguri, 
<collectingRegion id="49FEF8434544FFA828CBF9DD6E07F9F7" box="[1219,1367,1613,1636]" country="India" name="West Bengal" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">West Bengal</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F32D76314544FFA8296EF9DD6EF0F9F7" box="[1382,1440,1613,1636]" name="India" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">India</collectingCountry>
) is adjacent to that of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3A4D224544FFA82816F9FD6E49F917" authorityName="Tikader" authorityYear="1970" box="[1054,1305,1645,1668]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Platythomisus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bazarus">
<emphasis id="B94EEAB34544FFA82816F9FD6E49F917" box="[1054,1305,1645,1668]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Platythomisus bazarus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Nayabazar, West 
<collectingRegion id="49FEF8434544FFA82F6FF91D68E7F937" box="[871,951,1677,1700]" country="India" name="Sikkim" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Sikkim</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F32D76314544FFA82FCCF91D68AFF937" box="[964,1023,1677,1700]" name="India" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">India</collectingCountry>
). After comparing the descriptions and figures of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3A4D224544FFA82F91F93D6E62F957" authority="Tikader, 1970" authorityName="Tikader" authorityYear="1970" box="[921,1330,1709,1732]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Platythomisus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bazarus">
<emphasis id="B94EEAB34544FFA82F91F93D6FDEF957" box="[921,1166,1709,1732]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Platythomisus bazarus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFAB4B504544FFA82890F93D6E62F957" author="Tikader, B" box="[1176,1330,1709,1732]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" pagination="1 - 83" refId="ref7339" refString="Tikader, B. K., 1970. Spider fauna of Sikkim. Records of the Zoological Survey of India, 64: 1 - 83." type="journal article" year="1970">Tikader, 1970</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and those of our specimens (from 
<collectingCountry id="F32D76314544FFA82820F95D6F31F977" box="[1064,1121,1741,1764]" name="India" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">India</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F32D76314544FFA82864F95D6FE0F977" box="[1132,1200,1741,1764]" name="China" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">China</collectingCountry>
), it was found that they should be the same species. Both of our specimens bear the following diagnostic characters of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C3A4D224544FFA82904F89D6E0DF8B7" authorityName="Thorell" authorityYear="1877" box="[1292,1373,1805,1828]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Epidius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B94EEAB34544FFA82904F89D6E0DF8B7" box="[1292,1373,1805,1828]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Epidius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: tibiae and metatarsi of legs I &amp; II slender with thick ventral spines, epigyne with an atrium and a pairs of posterior sclerotized plates, eye arrangement also as same as that of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3A4D224544FFA82945F8FD6EF0F817" authorityName="Thorell" authorityYear="1877" box="[1357,1440,1901,1924]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Epidius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B94EEAB34544FFA82945F8FD6EF0F817" box="[1357,1440,1901,1924]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Epidius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Because of those, 
<taxonomicName id="4C3A4D224544FFA82FE8F81D6F9BF837" authorityName="Tikader" authorityYear="1970" box="[992,1227,1933,1956]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Platythomisus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bazarus">
<emphasis id="B94EEAB34544FFA82FE8F81D6F9BF837" box="[992,1227,1933,1956]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Platythomisus bazarus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be transferred to the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C3A4D224544FFA82FB3F83D6F5DF857" authorityName="Thorell" authorityYear="1877" box="[955,1037,1965,1988]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Epidius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B94EEAB34544FFA82FB3F83D6F5DF857" box="[955,1037,1965,1988]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Epidius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as 
<taxonomicName id="4C3A4D224544FFA82830F83D6EF4F857" authority="(Tikader, 1970)" authorityName="Tang &amp; Yin &amp; Peng &amp; Griswold" authorityYear="2009" baseAuthorityName="Tikader" baseAuthorityYear="1970" box="[1080,1444,1965,1988]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Epidius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bazarus" status="new combination">
<emphasis id="B94EEAB34544FFA82830F83D6FBAF857" box="[1080,1258,1965,1988]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Epidius bazarus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFAB4B504544FFA828F4F83D6ECBF857" author="Tikader, B" box="[1276,1435,1965,1988]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" pagination="1 - 83" refId="ref7339" refString="Tikader, B. K., 1970. Spider fauna of Sikkim. Records of the Zoological Survey of India, 64: 1 - 83." type="journal article" year="1970">Tikader, 1970</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A27D57C84544FFA82F20F85D68B6F877" box="[808,998,1997,2020]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" rank="species">new combination</taxonomicNameLabel>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
